# Coding Standards (Always Applied)

This rule file exists to prevent single-point patching and to keep fixes systemic.

## Fix the Class, Not the Instance (No Single-Point Patching)

Context: A user reports one visible bug (e.g. unreadable text in a single input). Treat that report as an example of a class of issues, not proof the problem is isolated.

Protocol:
1. Infer the root cause and the pattern/class.
2. Search the codebase for all instances of that pattern (same component, same context, same anti-pattern).
3. Fix all instances of the class, OR clearly document what’s in scope vs. what remains (with follow-ups).
4. Do not claim “done” after a one-point patch when the issue is clearly systemic.

Reference:
- `docs/CODING_STANDARDS.md` (canonical coding standards)
- `docs/operations/LEARNINGS.md` (incident + rationale)

